HEADWORD: Redoubtable
<hw>Re*doubt"a*ble</hw> <pr>(-?*b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>redoutable</ets>, formerly also spelt
<ets>redoubtable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Formidable; dread; terrible to foes;
<as>as, a <ex>redoubtable</ex> hero</as>; hence, valiant; -- often in
contempt or burlesque.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>redoutable</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redoubted</ent>⟦br⟧
